Executive Profile
Carolyn M. Tastad  Group President of North America Selling and Market Operations, The Procter & Gamble CompanyAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships56--
Background

		Ms. Carolyn M. Tastad has been the Group President of North America Selling and Market Operations at The Procter & Gamble Company since 2015. Ms. Tastad's extensive 30-year career in consumer goods at P&G has included roles in general management, acquisition integration and customer business development. She has held responsibilities at both the global and regional levels, living in the U.S., Canada and Switzerland. Ms. Tastad served as Global Head of Customer Business ... Development at The Procter & Gamble Company since February 1, 2014 until December 31, 2014. She served as the Vice President of Global Market Strategy & Planning and One Go-to-Market Optimization at The Procter & Gamble Company until February 1, 2014. She served as the Head of Cosmetics & Fragrance Division and Member of Management Board of Wella GmbH since July 2006. Ms. Tastad began her P&G career in 1983. She has deep experience leading sales and market development organizations for P&G businesses in the U.S., Canada, Europe and globally and has worked in a range of businesses including deep experience in Health and Beauty. She has been a Director at Kellogg Company since December 01, 2015. Ms. Tastad also serves on the boards of the Grocery Manufacturers Association and the Cincinnati Museum Center. She served on the Wella AG corporate board and several nonprofit boards in Canada.Read Full Background




